title: Sussan Ley faces climate showdown | 7NEWS
description: Liberal Party MPs and senators are meeting behind closed doors for crucial climate change and energy discussions that could determine Opposition Leader Sussan Ley's political future. The party room showdown focuses on reaching a unified position on net zero emissions amid deep divisions between moderate and conservative factions. Three Liberal colleagues experienced an additional challenge when their QantasLink flight made an emergency landing in Adelaide due to cockpit smoke before the critical meeting. title: Liberals vote on ditching net zero policy | 7NEWS
description: The Liberal Party is holding a crucial meeting in Parliament House where more than 50 senators and MPs are expected to vote on scrapping the net zero emissions by 2050 policy while maintaining commitment to the Paris Climate Agreement. Sussan Ley's leadership is under pressure following the Nationals' decision to abandon net zero 10 days earlier, with power prices having risen 39% since the policy was adopted in 2022. title: Qantas flight returns after smoke emergency | 7NEWS
description: A Qantas flight QF1972 from Adelaide to Canberra was forced to turn back shortly after takeoff when smoke filled the cabin. The aircraft, carrying 55 passengers including Liberal Party politicians Andrew McLaughlin, Tony Passant and Leah Blythe, landed safely with emergency services on standby. The captain issued a pan call to air traffic control, and all passengers were safely evacuated before continuing their journey to Canberra. title: Russia loses High Court embassy fight | 7NEWS
description: Russia has lost its High Court challenge against Australian legislation that cancelled its 99-year lease for a new embassy site near Parliament House in Canberra. The 2023 law allowed the Commonwealth to reclaim the block after Russia's lawyers argued the legislation was unconstitutional and claimed no national security threat existed. The High Court upheld the government's action but ruled Russia is entitled to compensation for the forceful takeover. title: Victoria introduces adult time for youth crime | 7NEWS
description: Victoria is introducing new 'adult time for adult crime' laws that will allow children as young as 14 to face life sentences for serious violent offences including aggravated home invasions and carjackings. The legislation follows Queensland's model and will see many young offenders tried in county court rather than children's court, which can only impose maximum three-year penalties. The Allan Government aims to pass the bill through Parliament by the end of the year, though it remains in draft form. title: Trump asks Supreme Court to overturn Carroll verdict | 7NEWS
description: Donald Trump has petitioned the US Supreme Court to overturn a 2023 civil jury verdict that found him liable for sexually abusing and defaming writer E. Jean Carroll. The case stems from Carroll's claim that Trump assaulted her in a Manhattan department store dressing room in 1996, for which she was awarded $7 million in damages. Trump's lawyers argue the allegations were supported by highly inflammatory evidence.
